Bongani Zungu of South Africa celebrate during the African Cup of Nations match between South Africa and Namibia at Al-Salam Stadium on June 28, 2019 in Cairo, Egypt. JOHANNESBURG - Bafana Bafana coach Stuart Baxter has announced his starting line-up ahead of South Africa's eagerly anticipated game against Morocco on Monday. South Africa need a win to progress through to the knockout phase or at least a draw and hope other results go their way. Morocco sits atop of Group D with six points and will bid to continue their flawless record at this year's tournament. READ: Bafana stay in hunt for last-16 spot after laboured win Meanwhile, second-placed Ivory Coast face Namibia. Starting line-up: Ronwen Williams; Thamsanqa Mkhize, Sfiso Hlanti, Buhle Mkhwanazi, Thulani Hlatshwayo (C); Kamohelo Mokotjo, Themba Zwane, Bongani Zungu, Thulani Serero; Lebo Mothiba, Percy Tau. Substitutes: Darren Keet, Bruce Bvuma, Ramahlwe Mphahlele, Daniel Cardoso, Hlompho Kekana, Sbusiso Vilakazi, Thembinkosi Lorch, Lars Veldwijk, Innocent Maela, Dean Furman, Lebogang Maboe. The Bafana game kicks off at 18h00 at the Al Salam Stadium.